PN,35606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FMultiple party sources say gloomy
OL,7,Finternal data suggests that heavy
OL,8,Flosses are expected across the
OL,9,Fcountry, including the northeast,
OL,10,Fwhere they made big advances a decade
OL,11,Fago.
OL,13,F"The south is the only part we may
OL,14,Fhold out under this polling," said one
OL,15,Fsource.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FThis largely chimes with public
OL,7,Fsurveys but Scottish Conservative
OL,8,Fleader Russell Findlay has declared
OL,9,Fthat just as his party defied pundits
OL,10,Ffive years ago to retain all 31 of its
OL,11,FMSPs, he believes he will do better
OL,12,Fthan expected once again.
OL,14,FMore optimistic are the Scottish
OL,15,FGreens. Co-leader Gillian Mackay said
OL,16,Fthey want an "MSP in every region" and
OL,17,Fare hopeful of returning a
OL,18,Frepresentative on the South Scotland
OL,19,Flist.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FBut the party is largely aiming its
OL,7,Fresources at urban areas and have
OL,8,Fidentified two target constituencies:
OL,9,FEdinburgh Central, currently held by
OL,10,Fconstitution secretary Angus
OL,11,FRobertson, and Nicola Sturgeon's
OL,12,Fformer seat of Glasgow Southside.
OL,14,FMeanwhile the Lib Dems are looking
OL,15,Fnorth and reckon they can win seats in
OL,16,Fthe Highlands on top of their existing
OL,17,Fpockets in the central belt and the
OL,18,Fnorthern isles.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FThey also hope a well-funded campaign
OL,7,Fwill deliver them an MSP on the South
OL,8,FScotland list.
OL,10,FThe Lib Dems see their former
OL,11,Fstronghold of the Borders as a massive
OL,12,Fgap in their armour and believe if
OL,13,Fthey gain representation there, they
OL,14,Fcan think once again about becoming a
OL,15,F"national party".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FIronically, Reform UK's potential to
OL,7,Fappear from nowhere and pick up seats
OL,8,Fin every part of the country `
OL,9,Fnotwithstanding its controversial
OL,10,Fcandidates ` is currently helping the
OL,11,Fparty that sees itself as Scotland's
OL,12,Ftruly national representatives: the
OL,13,FSNP.
OL,15,FDiffley said Reform is on course to
OL,16,Freturn between 15 and 20 MSPs, adding:
OL,17,F"It's shaken up the political world in
OL,18,FScotland as it has in other places in
OL,19,Fthe UK significantly as well.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,F"And what it means is because they are
OL,7,Ftaking votes almost exclusively from
OL,8,Fdisgruntled Labour and Conservative
OL,9,Fvoters, it makes the SNP's task much
OL,10,Feasier.
OL,12,F"So it means you can lose 25 per cent
OL,13,Fof your voters ` as the SNP has done
OL,14,Fsince 2021 ` but actually probably
OL,15,Fcome out on 35 per cent of the vote
OL,16,Fwith about the same number of seats in
OL,17,Fparliament as they got five years ago."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FThis is why John Swinney reckons he
OL,7,Fcan win a majority, which he says will
OL,8,Flead to a second independence
OL,9,Freferendum, despite the fall in
OL,10,Fsupport over the last five years.
OL,12,FThe first minister can look across
OL,13,Falmost all of Scotland's 73
OL,14,Fconstituencies and see winnable
OL,15,Fbattles.
OL,17,FThis is important when the magic
OL,18,Fmajority number is 65 MSPs.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G12/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FBut a wide and ` relatively to
OL,7,Fprevious elections ` shallow support
OL,8,Fbase has potential drawbacks, which
OL,9,Fwere highlighted at the last general
OL,10,Felection.
OL,12,FThe SNP won 30 per cent of the popular
OL,13,Fvote, compared to Labour's 5 per cent,
OL,14,Fbut only returned nine MPs when there
OL,15,Fwere 36 victorious candidates wearing
OL,16,Fred rosettes.
OL,18,FFive years on, nationalists still
OL,19,Fremember Galloway and West Dumfries -
OL,20,Fthe knife-edge seat that denied them
OL,21,Fgoing it alone at Holyrood.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G13/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,357,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F356A1774980702
OL,3,CWhy the South of Scotland is key to
OL,4,Cthis regional Holyrood election
OL,6,FA senior SNP source: "The south of
OL,7,FScotland could make or break our
OL,8,Fmajority. It's so finely balanced."
OL,10,FThe national picture is important, of
OL,11,Fcourse it is. But every serious
OL,12,Fpolitical party has realised that the
OL,13,Fkey to success, no matter how you
OL,14,Fmeasure it, is by focusing on and
OL,15,Fwinning the local battles.
OL,17,FHave you heard our new podcast Talking
OL,18,FPolitics? Every week Tom, Robert and
OL,19,FAnushka dig into the biggest issues
OL,20,Fdominating the political agenda...
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G14/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
